# Anvil GitHub fork

- **Fork:** https://github.com/hyperronropes/Anvil
- **Default remote:** `origin` → `https://github.com/hyperronropes/Anvil.git`
- **Default branch:** `master`
- **Local project:** `C:\Users\Shadow\Desktop\DeepCodev3-master`

## Push workflow

Only commit or push when the user explicitly asks (e.g. "push to my fork").

When asked to push:

1. Ensure Git is available (`git --version`).
2. `git status`, `git diff`, `git log -1` — review changes; never commit secrets (`.env`, API keys, `~/.Anvil/`).
3. Stage source changes only — never `dist/`, `build/_work/`, `app/node_modules/`, or build artifacts.
4. Commit with a clear message focused on why.
5. `git push -u origin master` (or current branch).

If the repo is not initialized, run once:

```powershell
cd C:\Users\Shadow\Desktop\DeepCodev3-master
git init
git remote add origin https://github.com/hyperronropes/Anvil.git
git branch -M master
```

First push to the fork may diverge heavily from upstream (rebrand `deepcodev3` → `anvil`). Prefer a normal push; only use force if the user explicitly requests it.
